excerpt: Family-owned establishment offering a selection of gourmet Mediterranean dishes in an elegant venue.
detail_description: Palazzo Preca Restaurant is a family-owned Mediterranean eatery located in an elegant venue. The restaurant offers a selection of gourmet dishes, including European, Italian, and vegetarian options. With its relaxed yet chic ambiance, Palazzo Preca is known for serving hearty local dishes. The restaurant's quaintly rustic interior design adds to the dining experience, making it a popular choice for families and those seeking fine dining with a unique Mediterranean flair.
name: Palazzo Preca Restaurant

excerpt: Traditional restaurant with dark wood & patterned tiles, offering regional dishes, steaks & pasta.
detail_description: Ta' Kris is a traditional restaurant located in a charming old bakery, featuring dark wood and patterned tiles that create a warm and rustic atmosphere. The menu offers a variety of regional dishes, including hearty options like rabbit stew, bragioli (beef olives), and lampuki pie (fish pie). Run by chef proprietor Chris, the restaurant retains the traditional colorful tile-work from the old bakery, adding to its authentic decor.
name: Ta' Kris

excerpt: Casual, Italian trattoria with simple decor serving Maltese fare, seafood specials & homemade pasta.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Valletta on Old Bakery Street, Rubino is a cozy Italian trattoria that offers a charming and intimate dining experience. Originally established as a confectionery in 1906, this family-run restaurant has evolved into a beloved bistro known for its classic Maltese and Italian dishes.
name: Rubino

detail_description: Guzé is a popular bistro housed in a 16th-century building with a low-key and inviting decor. The menu offers a variety of sea creatures, seasonal vegetables, and traditional Maltese favorite rabbit served in modern variations. The restaurant takes traditional, seasonal ingredients and presents them in new and exciting ways.
name: Guzé
address: 22 Old Bakery St, Valletta VLT 1454, Malta

detail_description: Nestled within the historic bastions of Valletta, Rampila Restaurant offers a unique dining experience that seamlessly blends history and luxury. Guests can choose to dine in a high-end restaurant or on the beautiful terrace, originally built by the Knights of St John and overlooking the city gate. The terrace, once a military tunnel and gun emplacement, now provides a peaceful setting for enjoying high-end cuisine or savoring a glass of wine.
name: Rampila Restaurant
address: St. John Cavalier, Ordnance St, Valletta VLT 1110, Malta

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Valletta, Malata Bar and Restaurant offers a delightful fusion of Maltese, French, and Mediterranean cuisines. Located just across from the Grand Masters Palace in St Georges Square, this charming eatery invites you to enjoy your meal either inside its historic 500-year-old cellar adorned with whimsical caricatures or outside on the lively square.
name: Malata Bar and Restaurant
address: St Georges Palace Square, Island of VLT1190,, Il-Belt Valletta, Malta

detail_description: Noni is a renowned restaurant located in Valletta's Republic Street, at the heart of the vibrant dining and entertainment scene. The establishment offers a blend of Maltese and Mediterranean cuisine with a modern French twist. Chef Jonathan Brincat has curated an elegant menu featuring dishes such as rabbit confit croquettes, slow-cooked octopus tagine, and te fit-tazza dessert.
name: Noni

detail_description: The Harbour Club, located in Valletta, is a Michelin-listed restaurant known for its creative and high-quality dishes, extensive wine selection, and excellent service. Situated alongside the charming harbourside, it offers picturesque views of the Grand Harbour. The restaurant's sleek terrace provides an ideal setting to savor French-influenced cuisine with a focus on seafood. The building's history as a warehouse adds to its unique charm, while live jazz music enhances the dining experience.
name: The Harbour Club

detail_description: Sole by Tarragon is a remarkable dining destination that builds on the esteemed legacy of its predecessor, Tarragon, which has been delighting guests since 2007. Nestled in the picturesque St. Paul’s Bay, this restaurant shines with a menu that emphasizes fresh local fish and high-quality ingredients, ensuring each dish is not only delicious but also elegantly presented. The culinary creations are crafted under the expert guidance of renowned chef Marvin Gauci, who infuses his creative flair into every plate.
name: Sole by Tarragon

detail_description: Chophouse is a renowned steakhouse in Sliema, Malta, known for offering a wide selection of the freshest cuts of succulent steaks, meats, and fish. It is considered one of the leading meat restaurants on the island and boasts the largest charcoal grill in Malta. The restaurant prides itself on grilling mouth-watering meats to perfection and crafting dishes with expertise by butchering, marinating, and aging the meats in-house.
name: Chophouse
address: Tigne Point, Censu Xerri, Sliema, Malta

detail_description: Tal-Petut Restaurant, located in Birgu, Malta, is a must-visit gem offering a unique dining experience. The restaurant provides an opportunity to savor traditional Maltese cuisine with a modern twist. Chef Donald and his team are passionate about showcasing the best local flavors and are eager to engage in conversations about their dishes. The charming and rustic atmosphere adds to the overall appeal of this dining destination.
name: Tal-Petut Restaurant

detail_description: Nenu The Artisan Baker in Valletta is a long-established restaurant that offers traditional Maltese favorites, including the opportunity for visitors to participate in 'Bake your own Ftira' sessions. The eatery welcomes both locals and tourists to savor authentic cuisine in a typical bakery setting. With various dining areas like the Courtyard and the Attic, it's suitable for special occasions and events.
name: Nenu The Artisan Baker Valletta
address: 143 St Domnic Street, Valletta VLT 1605, Malta

detail_description: Tartarun Restaurant, named after a type of Maltese fishing net, is a family-run establishment in the charming fishing village of Marsaxlokk. The restaurant takes its seafood seriously and offers a menu that highlights the local catch with traditional and innovative dishes. Fresh fish is brought in daily by local fishermen, ensuring high-quality cuisine with a focus on locally sourced ingredients.
name: Tartarun Restaurant

detail_description: Trattoria da Pippo is a beloved restaurant located in the heart of Valletta, offering a warm and inviting atmosphere that attracts both locals and visitors. With a menu that changes daily, this charming trattoria serves up traditional Maltese cuisine with influences from Italian and Sicilian flavors.
name: Trattoria da Pippo

detail_description: Gugar Hangout & BAR is a small, laid-back spot located at the lower end of Republic Street in Valletta. It's popular among the younger locals and offers a unique atmosphere with upcycled furnishings and a selection of alternative books to read. During the day, it serves wholesome food, refreshing smoothies, light sandwiches, soups, and chocolate balls. In the evening, it transforms into a proper hangout spot where you can enjoy drinks and delicious snacks.
name: Gugar Hangout & BAR

detail_description: Caviar & Bull, located within the Corinthia Beach Resort in Malta, is a premier destination for modern cuisine. Helmed by Chef Marvin Gauci, the restaurant offers a gastronomic menu featuring locally sourced ingredients such as Wagyu beef and fresh fish. The talented team creates an array of flavors inspired by land and sea, providing an immersive dining experience that ignites the senses. With a charming waterside location and stunning views of St.
name: Caviar & Bull
address: Corinthia Hotel St. George's Bay San Ġiljan, STJ 3301, Malta

detail_description: Legligin Restaurant, which translates to "one who drinks a lot," is a delightful restaurant and wine bar in Valletta, Malta. Nestled in the cellar of an original townhouse, the rustic ambiance is accentuated by red shutters, stone walls adorned with wine bottle holes, and an assortment of crockery. The establishment offers Maltese meze paired with a selection of over 30 exceptional wines.
name: Legligin Restaurant

detail_description: ION Harbour By Simon Rogan is a Michelin-starred restaurant located on the rooftop of Valletta's Iniala Harbour House. The restaurant offers a unique dining experience with French-inspired cuisine using the best seasonal Maltese ingredients. Guests can enjoy panoramic views of Valletta's Grand Harbour while indulging in exquisite dishes and an extensive wine list.
name: ION Harbour By Simon Rogan

detail_description: Zest Restaurant, a long-standing pillar of Malta's culinary scene, has been offering Asian fusion cuisine for over two decades. Recently, the menu has been enriched with Japanese-inspired Peruvian dishes, known as Nikkei Cuisine. This stylish restaurant at Hotel Juliani overlooks Spinola Bay and offers a mix of continental food alongside its innovative nikkei approach. The atmosphere is delightful and the staff is friendly, ensuring a fantastic dining experience.
name: Zest Restaurant
address: Hotel Juliani 25 Triq San Gorg St Julian's, STJ 3208, Malta

detail_description: Piccolo Padre is a family-friendly pizzeria and trattoria located in St Julians, Malta. Situated inside an 18th century Maltese villa with stunning views over Balluta Bay, this Italian restaurant offers a wide selection of dishes including freshly-baked pizzas, seafood, and steak. It's an ideal spot for a romantic dining experience or a meal with children. The restaurant is known for its excellent food, friendly service, and picturesque sea view.
name: Piccolo Padre

detail_description: Blue Elephant, located within the St Julians Hilton hotel, offers a delightful blend of sweet and spicy Asian cuisine. The restaurant takes pride in its beautifully presented dishes that capture the authentic flavors of Thailand. From spring rolls to spicy curries and Dim Sum, guests can savor a well-thought-out menu while enjoying views of the marina. With some seating overlooking the shipyard, Blue Elephant provides a romantic ambiance with its beautiful interior adorned with orchids and waterfalls.
name: Blue Elephant

detail_description: Root 81 is a popular restaurant located in Rabat, Malta. It offers a diverse menu with Italian, pizza, and international cuisine. The restaurant has received positive reviews for its food and dining experience. Visitors have praised the establishment for its Mediterranean and vegetarian options. Root 81 is recommended for special occasions such as wedding anniversaries and romantic dinners. The restaurant's location in Saqqajja Square makes it convenient for tourists exploring the area.
name: Root 81

detail_description: Venus Restaurant Bugibba is a popular dining spot offering delicious seafood and Mediterranean cuisine. With over 2,000 reviews, it's known for its excellent service and friendly staff. Located in Bugibba, Malta, it's a must-visit for those looking to enjoy top-notch dining experiences. Whether you're craving fresh seafood or flavorful Mediterranean dishes, Venus Restaurant is sure to delight your taste buds.
name: Venus Restaurant Bugibba
address: il, Triq Gandoffli, St Paul's Bay SPB10, Malta

detail_description: Il-Merill Restaurant, named after Malta's national songbird, the blue rock thrush, is a hidden gem located in a quiet street near Sliema's waterfront. This family-run restaurant offers an intimate and professionally managed dining experience with a wide selection of traditional Maltese and Mediterranean dishes. The generous portions ensure great value for money, making every visit memorable.
name: Il-Merill Restaurant

detail_description: The Submarine is a popular spot in Sliema, Malta known for its fresh and customizable sandwiches at a good price. It's a great place to stop by for lunch before heading to the nearby Three Cities. Visitors can enjoy exploring the charming alleyways and admiring the beautiful Maltese architecture in Cospicua, Vittoriosa, and Senglea.
name: The Submarine
address: Triq il-merkanti 42, Il-Belt Valletta VLT 1173, Malta

detail_description: D'Office Bistro is a charming restaurant and wine bar located in the heart of Valletta, Malta. The menu features a delightful selection of Mediterranean and European cuisine, all beautifully presented. The interior is adorned with an array of interesting collectibles, creating a captivating atmosphere for diners as they await their meals. Whether you choose to dine inside surrounded by unique decor or sit on the terrace, you can expect excellent service and fair prices for quality spirits and wines.
name: D'Office Bistro
address: No 132, Arch Bishop Street C/W 1 & 2 Fredrick Street, Il-Belt Valletta, Malta

detail_description: 67 Kapitali is a vibrant craft beer bar located in Valletta, Malta. It offers an extensive selection of beers, including local brews from Valletta and beyond. The bar is known for its create-your-own platters that feature a generous amount of delicious food perfect for sharing. In addition to the 11 beer taps and various cans and bottles, they also have a Spritz menu and a full cocktail bar.
name: 67 Kapitali
address: 67 Triq l-Ifran Il-Belt Valletta, VLT 1427, Malta

detail_description: Diar il-Bniet is a charming restaurant located in the village of Dingli, near the Dingli Cliffs and Mdina. The warm decor and welcoming staff create a homely atmosphere. They offer a variety of authentic Maltese dishes made with locally sourced ingredients, some of which are grown in the surrounding fields and also sold in their small shop. The restaurant prides itself on using exclusively local produce to create seasonal and fresh meals.
name: Diar il-Bniet

detail_description: Cafe Jubilee is a charming bistro with three locations across the Maltese islands, each boasting quirky decor adorned with vintage posters and curiosities hanging from the ceiling. The menu offers Mediterranean-inspired dishes such as soups, salads, sandwiches, and pastas, along with continental breakfast options. A must-try is the torta tal-lampuki, a popular dish at Cafe Jubilee.
name: Cafe Jubilee

detail_description: Ta' Marija is an iconic Maltese restaurant that showcases the country's vibrant and festive nature. The menu features authentic Maltese cuisine with subtle touches from a modern-day palate, and from traditional rabbit dishes to mouthwatering desserts, there's something to tempt every taste bud. The service is fast and the food generous, making Ta' Marija a must-go for anyone looking for a delicious gastronomic experience in Malta.
name: Ta' Marija - Your Gastro Maltese Kitchen since 1964

detail_description: Trabuxu Bistro, founded by Krista and Karl Fenech Soler, offers a complete Mediterranean experience through its warm-toned interiors and art pieces. The menu combines Italian and Mediterranean flavors to create a unique dining experience. Located in the heart of Valletta, the bistro provides an intimate ambiance and an exceptional wine selection within a centuries-old vaulted cellar.
name: Trabuxu Bistro
address: 8, 9 South St, Il-Belt Valletta VLT 1104, Malta

detail_description: Piadina Caffe is a charming cafe located near St Johns Co-Cathedral in Valletta, offering a delightful breakfast menu featuring fresh croissants, muesli, toasts with Italian hams, and their specialty piadina. This flatbread originates from the Emilia-Romagna region of Italy. The cafe is perfect for a leisurely morning or a quick lunch break, with limited seating inside but ample space on the long steps outside.
name: Piadina Caffe
address: 24, St.Lucia Street, Il-Belt Valletta VLT 1186, Malta

detail_description: Nestled in the charming streets of Valletta, Il-Horza Restaurant offers a cozy dining experience with a remarkable view of the Grand Harbour and Fort St. Angelo. The interior is adorned with wine bottles, adding to its quaint atmosphere. This small and friendly eatery serves Maltese classics for lunch, such as squash soup, pasta, and pork belly.
name: Il-Horza Restaurant
address: 6 St. Christopher's Street, Valletta VLT 1468, Malta

excerpt: Relaxed eatery serving Italian staples including pasta, meat dishes & desserts, plus wine & coffee.
detail_description: Zero Sei Trattoria Romana is a charming Italian eatery located in the heart of Valletta, offering a relaxed atmosphere and authentic Roman cuisine. The restaurant is known for its classic dishes such as carbonara and cacio e pepe, prepared using traditional recipes passed down through generations. While it's beloved for its delicious food, it's important to note that they may not be suitable for those with severe gluten intolerance due to potential cross-contamination in the kitchen.
name: Zero Sei Trattoria Romana

detail_description: Nestled along Balluta Bay, Wigi's Kitchen may not catch your eye from the outside, but its charming interior and delectable offerings are sure to impress. This family-run restaurant offers a diverse menu with options for every craving at reasonable prices. Specializing in savory steaks and delightful desserts, this unassuming beachside eatery surprises diners with its culinary prowess. With a focus on meats and seafood, Wigi's Kitchen has garnered praise for its expertly prepared dishes.
name: Wigi's Kitchen
address: Triq Censu Tabone St.Julians, STJ 1217, Malta

detail_description: Zeri's is a Mediterranean restaurant located in the upscale area of Portomaso, Malta. The menu features a blend of traditional Mediterranean dishes with oriental fusion, crafted by Chef Patron Mark Zerafa, also known as Zeri. The sleek and modern decor offers a trendy atmosphere with spectacular sea views. Known for its warm ambiance and delectable Mediterranean cuisine, particularly fresh seafood, Zeri's has become a favorite among locals and tourists alike.
name: Zeri's

detail_description: Bianco's Pizza & Pasta is a popular Italian restaurant located in St Julians, Malta. Situated near the marina, it offers a cozy and traditional ambiance along with generous portions of hearty Italian cuisine. The restaurant also hosts various day parties, adding to the vibrant atmosphere of the area.
name: Bianco's Pizza & Pasta
address: St George's Road, St Julian's, Malta

detail_description: Tosca Restaurant is situated in the heart of Mellieha, within the 4* Solana Hotel & Spa. The restaurant offers a seasonal American menu with influences from global traditions and local ingredients, some of which are sourced from their rooftop garden. It provides both indoor and outdoor seating areas, creating the perfect ambiance to savor their cuisine. Additionally, it is wheelchair accessible, catering to individuals with special needs.
name: Trattoria Tosca
address: Gorg Borg Olivier Street, Il-Mellieħa MLH 1025, Malta

detail_description: Commando Restaurant is situated in Mellieha, a charming Maltese village, and is housed in a beautifully converted old building. The restaurant has retained much of its original character and offers a stunning setting with elegantly laid tables. It is nestled within a tastefully-restored 300-year-old building and boasts a proud culinary tradition dating back to the wartime 1930s.
name: Commando Restaurant
address: 1, Misraħ Iz-Żjara tal-Papa, Mellieħa MLH 1080, Malta

detail_description: De Mondion Restaurant is one of the top restaurants in Mdina, Central Malta, offering Mediterranean and Middle Eastern cuisine. It has been recognized as a must-visit dining destination, alongside other renowned eateries in the area. The restaurant's culinary offerings have garnered praise and accolades, making it a popular choice among locals and visitors alike. With its exquisite dishes and inviting ambiance, De Mondion Restaurant provides a delightful dining experience that captures the essence of the region's vibrant food scene.
name: The de Mondion Restaurant

detail_description: The Fork and Cork restaurant offers a Mediterranean and European menu, located about 3.6 km away from the Percy Jackson Book Order. It is known for bringing out the carnivore in the omnivore with its juicy steaks, creating a true connection with nature. The restaurant provides a dense, nutty cake filled with flavors from almonds, honey, and orange rinds - a rich indulgence often served during weddings and celebrations.
name: The Fork and Cork Restaurant

detail_description: Nestled within the historic fortifications of Mdina, Bacchus Restaurant offers a unique dining experience that beautifully marries history with culinary delight. Housed in two vaulted chambers that once served as gunpowder storage units from the 17th century, this atmospheric venue invites guests to indulge in a diverse array of Mediterranean dishes. From succulent veal medallions to fresh seabass and tender lamb belly, Bacchus caters to various palates while providing an enchanting backdrop steeped in history.
name: Bacchus Restaurant

detail_description: The Medina Restaurant is a hidden gem located in the narrow streets of Mdina, Malta. This 500-year-old restaurant offers a unique dining experience beneath vaulted stone ceilings or in an internal courtyard next to an ancient vine. It is known for its Mediterranean cuisine and charming ambiance. The restaurant has received accolades and recognition from various sources, making it a must-visit for those exploring the culinary scene in Mdina.
name: The Medina Restaurant
address: Holy Cross Street Mdina MT MDN, 1231, L-Imdina, Malta

detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Valletta on Archbishop Street, Ambrosia Maltese Bistronomy is a charming eatery that specializes in homemade comfort food crafted from locally sourced ingredients. The menu boasts an array of delightful options, including hearty vegetable soup, creamy mac and cheese, fresh salads, and a variety of traditional Maltese dishes. Diners rave about the generous portions and the must-try cheesecake that perfectly rounds off any meal.
name: Ambrosia Maltese Bistronomy

excerpt: Modern chain restaurant with a cheerful vibe, serving up seafood & sharing platters.
detail_description: Ocean Basket is a modern seafood chain restaurant with a lively atmosphere, offering generous portions of local seafood served in various forms from sushi to oysters. The menu is extensive and includes sharing platters of piping hot grilled dishes. The waitstaff provides a warm welcome, and the restaurant offers beautiful views in a lovely city zone. While the prices may be slightly high, it's considered an excellent choice for those craving delicious seafood and good service.
name: Ocean Basket
address: Qawra Road Qawra Saint Pauls Bay SPB, 1905, Malta

detail_description: Dimitri Valletta is a charming boutique restaurant that resides in a historic 450-year-old building, just a short stroll from the iconic Auberge de Castille. This delightful eatery offers diners an exquisite culinary adventure, showcasing flavors from Malta, Italy, Spain, and the United Kingdom. The menu is thoughtfully updated with each season to highlight fresh ingredients and surprise guests with innovative dishes.
name: Dimitri Valletta

detail_description: Napoletan pizza restaurant NapolEat serves up some of the best pizza in Malta, with a unique Verace style that is soft and fluffy. The dough is like heaven, and highly recommended. You can also enjoy pasta dishes, sandwiches, and other Mediterranean favourites at this popular spot. Delivery and takeout are available, as well as reservations for outdoor seating.
name: NapolEat
address: Dragonara Road San Julian, STJ 3140, Malta

detail_description: Naan Bar is an Indian restaurant and cocktail bar situated in the bustling area of Valletta on Old Bakery Street, which has become a sought-after dining spot in Malta. The venue features two levels, with a lively bar on the ground floor offering small plates and creative cocktails, while the lower level houses intimate dining spaces including a chef's table overlooking the show kitchen.
name: Naan Bar
address: 60/1 Melita Street Corner of, Old Bakery St, Valletta VLT 1450, Malta

excerpt: Stylish destination spotlighting Japanese snacks, sushi & specialties in a loungey atmosphere.
detail_description: AKI is a stylish Japanese restaurant and lounge bar located in the heart of Valletta, Malta. It offers a contemporary dining experience with a focus on Japanese snacks, sushi, and specialties in a relaxed atmosphere. The restaurant has been recognized by the Michelin Guide Malta 2022, showcasing its commitment to quality and innovation in its cuisine. With signature Japanese-inspired dishes prepared with care and modern palates in mind, AKI provides an ideal setting for enjoying an evening out.
name: AKI
address: 175 Strait St Corner of St. Street and Santa Lucia St Valletta, VLT 1455, Malta
